  <h2>Orange Wine - A Natural Wine Style</h2>

  <p>Orange wines are white grapes fermented with skin contact, often associated with natural winemaking:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>**Extended skin contact** creates amber color</li>
    <li>**Increased tannins** from grape skins</li>
    <li>**Complex, often polarizing flavors**</li>
    <li>**Ancient winemaking technique**</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Food Pairing with Natural Wines</h2>

  <h3>General Principles</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Natural wines often pair well with natural, unprocessed foods</li>
    <li>The earthy character complements vegetable-forward dishes</li>
    <li>High acidity works well with fermented foods</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Specific Pairings</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>**Natural white wines**: Raw seafood, goat cheese, vegetable dishes</li>
    <li>**Natural red wines**: Grilled vegetables, charcuterie, mushroom dishes</li>
    <li>**Orange wines**: Spiced dishes, aged cheeses, complex preparations</li>
  </ul>

